        <h1>Blood Donation Guide</h1>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Preparing for Donation</h2>
            <p>Before donating blood, it's important to prepare properly. Follow these steps:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Get a good night's sleep before the donation.</li>
                <li>Eat a healthy meal and stay hydrated.</li>
                <li>Avoid fatty foods such as fried or greasy items.</li>
                <li>Wear comfortable clothing with sleeves that can be rolled up.</li>
                <li>Bring a photo ID with you to the donation center.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>The Donation Process</h2>
            <p>Here's what to expect during the blood donation:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>You'll first complete a health questionnaire and a brief physical examination.</li>
                <li>Once cleared, you’ll sit comfortably while a nurse cleans your arm and inserts a needle.</li>
                <li>During the donation, you’ll be encouraged to relax and stay calm. The process usually takes about 8-10 minutes.</li>
                <li>After donation, the needle will be removed, and a bandage will be placed on your arm.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>After Donation Care</h2>
            <p>After donating blood, follow these guidelines for proper care:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Rest for a few minutes and enjoy some refreshments provided by the donation center.</li>
                <li>Drink plenty of fluids over the next 24 hours to stay hydrated.</li>
                <li>Avoid strenuous activities or heavy lifting for the rest of the day.</li>
                <li>If you experience any unusual symptoms, contact the donation center immediately.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section class="tips">
            <h2>Donation Tips</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Make sure you are feeling well on the day of your donation.</li>
                <li>Consider scheduling your donation appointment in advance.</li>
                <li>Tell the staff about any concerns or questions you have before the donation.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <div class="footer">
            <p>Thank you for considering donating blood! Your contribution can save lives.</p>
